Package command

Interface ICommand

All Known Implementing Classes:
AddEventPerformanceCommand, BookEventCommand, CancelBookingCommand, CancelEventCommand, CreateEventCommand, CreateNonTicketedEventCommand, CreateTicketedEventCommand, GetAvailablePerformanceTicketsCommand, GovernmentReport1Command, GovernmentReport2Command, ListConsumerBookingsCommand, ListEventBookingsCommand, ListEventsCommand, ListEventsOnGivenDateCommand, ListSponsorshipRequestsCommand, LoginCommand, LogoutCommand, RegisterConsumerCommand, RegisterEntertainmentProviderCommand, RespondSponsorshipCommand, UpdateConsumerProfileCommand, UpdateEntertainmentProviderProfileCommand, UpdateProfileCommand
public interface ICommand
ICommand is the interface implemented by all commands. This common interface allows the Controller to run any command using a single common method Controller.runCommand(ICommand).

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void execute​(Context context)
    This method should not be called directly outside of testing.
    Object getResult()
    Get the result from the latest run of the command.

  • Method Details

    • execute

      void execute​(Context context)
      This method should not be called directly outside of testing. Normal usage is to create a command object and execute it by passing to Controller.runCommand(ICommand) instead.
      Parameters:
      context - object that provides access to global application state

    • getResult

      Object getResult()
      Get the result from the latest run of the command.
      Returns:
      The command result (type varies by command) if successful and null or false otherwise.
